   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Message Five The Reality of the Kingdom of the Heavens</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>the Expansion of Christ the King Scripture Reading: Matt 21:5; 25:34; 13:3;</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Mark 4:26-29; Luke 17:20-21; Matt 5:3 Like the church and the New Jerusalem, the kingdom is a corporate person the enlargement and expansion of Christ the King Dan 2:34-35, 44-45: The church is Christ s increase in life; the kingdom is Christ s increase in administration John 3:29-30a; 1 Cor 12:12; Dan 2:34-35, 44-45.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Through the King s gaining us and our gaining Him, we and the King become the kingdom Mark 10:15; Col 2:6; 1:12-13; Rev 5:9-10; 1:6, 9.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>We are the kingdom because we are Christ s expansion, His enlargement Dan 2:34, 35b, 44; Rev 1:6.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>At the Lord s coming back, the corporate Christ, Christ with His overcomers, will become a great mountain to fill the whole earth, making the whole earth God s kingdom Dan 2:35b; Rev 11:15.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The reality of the kingdom of the heavens is Christ Himself Luke 17:20-21; Isa 9:6-7: The kingdom of the heavens is not something apart from Christ; the kingdom of the heavens is the person of the King Matt 2:2; 21:5; Rev 19:16.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>We need spiritual eyes to see that the kingdom is actually the wonderful Christ Luke 17:21b: We cannot have the kingdom of the heavens without Christ; where Christ is, there the kingdom of the heavens is also Matt 16:16, 18-19.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The kingdom of the heavens is actually the Lord Himself as the kingship within us Isa 32:1a.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The kingdom of God is the reality of the Spirit of God, which is the reality of Christ Matt 12:28: The Spirit is the reality of the Lord Jesus, for the Spirit is His person, and His person is His reality 1 Cor 6:11b.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>To have the kingdom in reality is to have a spiritual realization of the Lord Jesus Isa 6:5; John 12:41; Isa 33:17; 1 Cor 15:45b; 2 Cor 3:17a.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The reality of the kingdom of the heavens is the all-inclusive Christ sowing Himself into His believers as the seed of the kingdom and growing within them Matt 13:3; Mark 4:26-29: The King came as a Sower to sow Himself as the seed of the kingdom into our being; the King, the kingdom, and the seed of the kingdom are all Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The Triune God in humanity is the seed of the kingdom sown into God s chosen people that He might grow in them, live in them, and be expressed from within them to develop into God s ruling realm Col 2:9; Mark 4:26-29.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>The basic element of the reality of the kingdom is Christ Himself as the seed of life Matt 13:24, 37: The kingdom is wholly a matter of life Christ Himself as the seed of life, the seed of the kingdom, sown into our being Luke 8:8a, 15.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The reality of the kingdom of the heavens is the enlargement of Christ, the multiplication of Christ, as the seed sown into us Mark 4:26-29.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>The establishment of the kingdom is absolutely a matter of growth in life; to establish the kingdom is to grow the kingdom v. 27; 1 Cor 3:6-7, 9b.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Christ establishes the kingdom not by fighting or by teaching but by sowing Himself as the seed of life into believing people so that the kingdom of the heavens may grow up Matt 13:3-4a: The growth of Christ as the seed of life within us is the process of the kingdom Mark 4:26-29.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The kingdom is not established by our outward working but by the inward growing of Christ as the seed of life 1 Pet 1:23; 2 Pet 1:5-11.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>The reality of the kingdom of the heavens is Christ as the life-giving Spirit ruling within us 1 Cor 15:45b; 2 Cor 3:17a; 1 Cor 6:17; Matt 5:3: Jesus, the King, intends to be born in us, set up the throne of David in our heart, and establish His kingdom within us Luke 1:31-33.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>The Lord Jesus came as a King not to rule over us in an outward way but to enter into us in order to impart Himself into us that He might discharge our rebellious element and replace it with Himself John 6:15; 1:12-13.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>The basic thought of the Gospel of Matthew is that we must repent of not being in the kingdom and of not being under the kingship and authority of Christ Matt 3:2; 4:17.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>The Christ who enters into our spirit is the King with the kingdom, and now we are under a rule that is with the heavenly nature 2 Tim 4:22a; Matt 5:3: When Christ came into our spirit, the kingdom came with Him; the One within us is our King with the kingdom.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>Because the kingdom is within us, we are subdued, controlled, and ruled by the indwelling King Rom 8:9-10.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>The heavenly rule in our spirit is Christ, the living One, consummated as the life-giving Spirit 2 Cor 13:5b; 1 Cor 15:45b.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>The life-giving Spirit dwelling in us is the heavenly rule within us, and this heavenly rule is actually the kingdom of the heavens.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>The way for us to become the reality of the kingdom of the heavens is to eat Christ as our bread Matt 15:26-27, 32-37: God s economy is not a matter of outward things but of Christ coming into us inwardly; for this, we need to take Christ in by eating Him Eph 3:17a.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>As the heavenly King, Christ rules over us by feeding us with Himself as bread John 6:15, 32-35: We can be the reality of the kingdom of the heavens only by being nourished with Christ as our food Matt 15:26-27, 32-37.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>The Lord Jesus is the kingdom of obedience; we need to take Him in by eating Him as our bread so that He may be wrought into us Phil 2:8.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>The more we eat Christ as our bread, the more the royal ingredients in this bread are constituted into us to become the ruling element within us.</S>
   </TEXT>
